The paper presents a machine learning algorithm for one-class classification, which involves using regression models to address the problem of having only one class in the training data. This algorithm can be applied to various types of datasets, including image datasets. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.CV (Computer Vision). Additionally, the paper involves computing outlier scores, which suggests that it could also be relevant to the sub-categories cs.DM (Data Mining) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
